main event: Mrs. Russell observed an oval-shaped object with lights hovering above her residence in Mequon, Wisconsin on May 9, 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 3 to 4 minutes before the object moved off rapidly to the west., The object emitted a humming noise during the sighting., The observation was made under clear skies with sparse clouds., The object could not be identified as any conventional aircraft or known natural phenomenon., There was no physical evidence found to corroborate the sighting.
